CannaWry

CannaWry is a Ransomware developed in Python with an intention to understand the 2016 WannaCry Ransomware attack. This Ransomware encrypts the target machine entirely with a randomly created key, logged, until a simulated ransom is paid. This uses PyCrypto module to encrypt files.
